2. Newsletters & Substack Articles

2.1 Kevin Indig — Growth Memo
Publication: Growth Memo (kevin-indig.com)
Subscribers: 21,000+
Research Period: February – March 2026
Dataset: 846,000 sessions clickstream data

Primary research findings:
•	AI Mode behaviour: users accept the shortlist and click nothing else. Near-zero lateral clicks.
•	AI Overview behaviour: comparison mode. 47.5% of users scroll backward after the overview to evaluate organic results.
•	AI Mode optimisation is a visibility problem at the model layer — getting into the model’s training or retrieval set.
•	AI Overview optimisation is a comparison problem on the SERP itself — being the preferred result among surfaced options.
•	Keyword universe framework: maps when to optimise for models vs. humans based on query type.
“AI Mode optimization is a visibility problem at the model layer. AI Overview optimization is a comparison problem on the SERP itself.”
Advised brands: Ramp, Reddit, Snapchat, Dropbox. Podcast: Tech Bound (Spotify).

